Completed security improvements for Movie Time application:

1. Fixed critical credential exposure:
   - Replaced real database credentials and OMDB API key in .env with placeholders
   - Created .env.example with template values
   - Verified .gitignore already excludes .env

2. Fixed CSRF protection:
   - Uncommented CSRF token in views/add.ejs form
   - Added CSRF token to delete form in views/index.ejs
   - Fixed CSRF middleware ordering in app.js (moved csrfErrorHandler to come AFTER routes)
   - Enhanced CSRF cookie security with httpOnly, sameSite:strict, and secure flag for production

3. Verified existing security measures:
   - Helmet.js security headers active
   - Rate limiting configured (100 req/15min/IP)
   - Input validation in place
   - SQL injection protection via parameterized queries
   - XSS protection via EJS auto-escaping
   - Environment validation in config

All immediate security tasks completed. Application now has proper CSRF protection for all state-changing operations and credentials are no longer exposed in version control.